headline: Hubbell (HUBB): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q3 Earnings?
summary: Since January 2020, the S&P 500 has delivered a total return of 81.4%. But one standout stock has more than doubled the market - over the past five years, Hubbell has surged 179% to $415.01 per share. Its momentum hasn’t stopped as it’s also gained 13.4% in the last six months, beating the S&P by 6.1%.
